    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Daggers widely used by German and Swiss landsknechts during the 16th century, having a hilt, often of steel, with a grip which flares at the top and a guard with a shell or side ring and two quillons, either straight or curving towards the blade. They were furnished with a sheath, typically made of metal and decorated with raised bands.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dagas ampliamente usadas por lansquenetes alemanes y suizos durante el siglo XVI; tienen un puño, a menudo de acero, con una empuñadura que se ensancha en la parte superior y una guarnición con una concha o argolla lateral y dos gavilanes, indistintamente derechas o curvándose hacia la hoja. Estaban provistas de una vaina, por lo común de metal y decorada con franjas en relieve.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dolken met afhangende stootplaten, in één geheel ontworpen met de metalen scheden, die voorzien zijn van geprononceerde ringen of banden; gebruikt door Duitse en Zwitserse landsknechten in de 16e eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在十六世紀廣為德國與瑞士雇佣兵所使用的匕首，通常為鋼製的匕柄，把手在頂端呈喇叭狀展開，匕鍔則帶有罩子或側環，以及兩道護手鍔叉，呈筆直狀或呈弧形朝向匕刃。附有鞘套，通常為金屬製，並且有浮雕的帶狀裝飾。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
